HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 208
BY REPRESENTATIVE DICKERSON
HIGHWAYS: Urges and requests that the Department of Transportation and Development
to construct a roundabout on Louisiana Highway 1019
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To urge and request the Department of Transportation and Development to construct a
3 roundabout on Louisiana Highway 1019 near Old Louisiana Highway 16.
4 WHEREAS, roundabouts can improve the safety, operations, and aesthetics of an
5 intersection; and
6 WHEREAS, according to the Federal Highway Administration, roundabouts save
7 lives by reducing fatalities by up to ninety percent by reducing injury crashes up to seventy-
8 six percent and pedestrian crashes up to forty percent; and
9 WHEREAS, a traditional four-way intersection has thirty-two potential vehicle
10 conflict points, however, a single-lane roundabout has only eight, significantly lowering the
11 chance of collisions; and
12 WHEREAS, the circular design virtually eliminates high-speed, head-on, and
13 "T-bone" (right-angle) collisions, which are the most deadly types of intersection accidents;
14 and
15 WHEREAS, the shape of roundabouts forces drivers to slow to fifteen to twenty-five
16 miles per hour, which affords drivers more time to react to other road users and making any
17 resulting crashes far less severe; and
18 WHEREAS, there is only a stop sign on Louisiana Highway 1019 (LA-1019) at the
19 intersection of Old Louisiana Highway 16 (Old LA-16), resulting in a lack of traffic
20 regulation; and
